Poison example

Week 3

1 Overview

In a certain experiment, animals were exposed to one of three different poisons and four different treatments and the survival time recorded for each animal. Four animals were observed at each treatment/poison combination so that the experiment would be described as a \(3\times 4\) factorial experiment with replication 4.

2 Read in data

2.1 Libs

pacman::p_load(tidyverse, gglm)

2.2 Data

data(BoxCox, package = "Rfit")

3 Clean data

poison <- tibble(BoxCox)
poison
poison %>% count(Poison)
poison <- 
  poison %>% 
  mutate(
    Poison = case_when(
      Poison == 1 ~ "A",
      Poison == 2 ~ "B",
      Poison == 3 ~ "C", 
      TRUE ~ "Unknown"
    )
  )
poison
poison %>% count(Treatment)
poison <- 
  poison %>% 
  mutate(
    Treatment = case_when(
      Treatment == 1 ~ "a",
      Treatment == 2 ~ "b",
      Treatment == 3 ~ "c", 
      Treatment == 4 ~ "d", 
      TRUE ~ "Unknown"
    )
  )
poison
poison <- 
  poison %>% 
  mutate(
    across(
      where(is.character), 
      factor
    )
  )
poison

get_mean_recip <- function(x){
  mean(1/x)
}
grp_A_mean <- 
  poison %>% 
  filter(Poison == "A") %>% 
  pull(logSurv) %>% 
  get_mean_recip()
grp_A_mean
## [1] 1.800688
poison %>% 
  group_by(Poison) %>% 
  summarise(grp_mean = mean(1/logSurv)) %>% 
  mutate(
    grp_mean - grp_A_mean
  )
poison_lm2 <- lm(1 / logSurv ~ Poison + Treatment, 
                 data = poison,
